Better Pythonic way
st = "Jahnavi Durga"
print(st[::-1])

"Strings are Immutable, We cannot change them 'inplace' so we can use this below method "
st = "Jahnavi Durga"
st = list(st)
l, r = 0, len(st) - 1
while l < r:
    st[l], st[r] = st[r], st[l]
    l += 1
    r -= 1
st = "".join(st)
print(st)

Note: "Strings are immutable in python, so true inplace reversal is not possible . i'll convert it into a list and reverse using two pointers and convert back "
